CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 12, 1955, pg. 11 reads: "AKAS Plan - Shown cementing plans for the AKA's fourth annual Cotillion are, left to right: Mrs. Victoria C. Hargon, basileus, Alpha Omega Chapter; Gwendolyn Young, general chairman, and Geraldine Reynolds, chairman of the patrons' and sponsors' committee. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Alpha Kappa Alpha members Victoria C. Hargon, Gwendolyn Young, and Geraldine Reynolds, planning fourth annual Cotillion, gathered in interior, possibly Gateway Plaza, with shield with crown and two swords decoration, floral rug, and dark sofa with crown
